<HEAD>With PM-Textile Bill Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here at a glance are provisions of the textile trade legislation approved Friday by the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>: TEXTILE AND APPAREL IMPORTS Freezes overall textile and apparel imports this year at 1987 levels and limits future growth to one percent annually. NONRUBBER FOOTWEAR IMPORTS Freezes overall imports of nonrubber footwear at 1987 levels with no provision for increases in the future. AGRICULTURAL PROVISION Provides for preferred trade treatment for countries that increase their purchases of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> agricultural goods. AUCTIONED QUOTAS Requires the government to auction off import quotas among American importing companies. COMPENSATION Authorizes the president to negotiate reduced tariffs to compensate countries hurt by tightened import restraints.
