<HEAD>Landslides Bury 13</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Thirteen people have been buried in landslides caused by torrential rains in a village west of <LOCATION> Katmandu </LOCATION>, officials said. The landslides occurred Wednesday in <LOCATION> Pangrang </LOCATION> village, 112 miles west of <LOCATION> Katmandu </LOCATION>. Assistant Minister of Works and Transport <PERSON> Chhetra </PERSON> <PERSON> Bahadur </PERSON> <PERSON> Gurung </PERSON> said Friday that only five bodies had been recovered from the debris, and rescuers were workin to find the other eight known to have died, including a pregnant woman. <PERSON> Gurung </PERSON> said 30 villagers were injured in the landslides, including three who were airlifted to nearby <LOCATION> Pokhara </LOCATION> town for medical treatment.
