<FIRST>r w PM-CavazosHearing     09-10 0530</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cavazos Hearing,520</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nominee for Education Secretary Assured of Easy Confirmation</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto WX6</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JENNIFER DIXON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Lauro </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON> says it's time Americans `` start caring'' about the educational needs of all citizens, and he is promising to put the focus on the issue if confirmed as the next education secretary. `` I know this wo n't be turned around in a decade. We ca n't wait any longer. We've waited too long,'' <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> as it considered his nomination Friday to replace outgoing Education Secretary <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bennett </PERSON>. If sworn in, <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON> would become the first Hispanic member of a president's <ORGANIZATION> Cabinet </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON>, 61, appeared headed for an easy confirmation, with senators praising the son of a cattle foreman on the King Ranch in <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> who went on to become president of <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tech </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>. He became the first Hispanic and the first graduate of the school to hold the post with his selection in 1980. `` He is eminently qualified for this appointment with considerable experience in higher education,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Claiborne </PERSON> <PERSON> Pell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-R.I. </LOCATION> `` And in view of the fact that he has 10 children between the ages of 21 and 31, he has also had a central investment in elementary and secondary education.'' <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kennedy </PERSON>, D-Mass., said he was impressed and reassured by <PERSON> Cavazos </PERSON>' testimony that he would fight for increased spending and for making the <ORGANIZATION