ing for a day, forecaster <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Zimmer </PERSON> said. `` It could have been worse,'' he said, noting that early September is the height of the hurricane season, when wind and warm water conditions are ideal for storm development. <LOCATION> Florence </LOCATION>, the sixth named storm of the 1988 <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> season, is the second hurricane. The first, <PERSON> Debby </PERSON>, reached minimal hurricane strength briefly before hitting the coast of <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> last month.
