<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Ignace </PERSON> <PERSON> Dhellemmes </PERSON>, the French missionary known as the `` father of the pygmies,'' died Wednesday at age 74. <PERSON> Dhellemmes </PERSON> worked from 1948 to 1952 in a leper colony in eastern <LOCATION> Cameroon </LOCATION>. He began working among pygmy tribes in 1953. In a 1985 autobiography, <PERSON> Dhellemmes </PERSON> described his 40 years of work in <LOCATION> Cameroon </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Congo </LOCATION>, where he sought to improve the health and social welfare of pygmy tribes.
