<HEAD>Two `Stern Group' Members Admit They Helped Kill Bernadotte</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Two former members of a militant Jewish group which was led by the now-Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> admitted they helped kill a Swedish <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> envoy to <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> 40 years ago, an <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> journalist said today. It was the first time that members of the underground group, <ORGANIZATION> Lohamei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herut </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yisrael </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Freedom </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fighters </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-, also widely known as the `` Stern Group,'' confessed to the 1948 killing of Count <PERSON> Folke </PERSON> <PERSON> Bernadotte </PERSON>, said <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s state-run <ORGANIZATION> Educational </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> told The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> his information was based on interviews he conducted with <PERSON> Yehoshua </PERSON> <PERSON> Zetler </PERSON> and <PERSON> Meshulam </PERSON> <PERSON> Makover </PERSON>, two of <PERSON> Bernadotte </PERSON>'s killers. One of the interviews was shown Friday on Educational TV. The radical <ORGANIZATION> Lohamei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herut </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yisrael </ORGANIZATION> group, headed by <PERSON> Avraham </PERSON> <PERSON> Stern </PERSON>, was a splinter faction of the more mainstream group <ORGANIZATION> Irgun </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zvai </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Leumi </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Military </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> -RRB-. The faction advocated guerrilla rebellion against British rule in mandate <LOCATION> Palestine </LOCATION>. In 1942, <PERSON> Stern </PERSON> was shot and killed by the British police, and <PERSON> Lohamei </PERSON> <PERSON> Herut </PERSON> <PERSON> Yisrael </PERSON> devised a three-man leadership of <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>, <PERSON> Yisrael </PERSON> <PERSON> Scheib-Eldad </PERSON> and <PERSON> Natan </PERSON> <PERSON> Yellin-Mor </PERSON>, with <PERSON> Eldad </PERSON> serving as the group's ideologist. <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> quoted <PERSON> Zetler </PERSON> as saying he decided to kill <PERSON> Bernadotte </PERSON>, President of the Swedish <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cross </ORGANIZATION> during and after the World War II, after the envoy raised far-reaching Palestine partition ideas. <PERSON> Bernadotte </PERSON> was appointed in May 1948 to negotiate a cease-fire and recommend a settlement in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s 1948 War of Independence. `` <PERSON> Zetler </PERSON> said he conferred with <PERSON> Eldad </PERSON>, and the two traveled to <LOCATION> Haifa </LOCATION> to discuss it with Yellin-Mor. Yellin-Mor demanded that after the killing, the <ORGANIZATION> Lohamei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Herut </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Yisrael </ORGANIZATION> deny its role and blame the slaying on a tiny group of zealots called <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Homeland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Zetler </PERSON> returned to <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> and selected three men to join him and Makover on the mission: the late <PERSON> Yehoshua </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON>, <PERSON> Ben </PERSON> <PERSON> Moshe </PERSON> and another man, `` who is still alive but refuses to disclose his identity,'' <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> said. `` They call him -LRB- the fifth man -RRB- the <LOCATION> Gingi </LOCATION>, or the red-haired one,'' <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Margalit </PERSON> quoted <PERSON> Makover </PERSON> as saying th