<HEAD>Dwarf Loves Being Tossed Around, Ignores Criticism From Other
Little People</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> loves getting thrown around in dwarf-tossing contests, and shrugs off bitter criticisms of the practice by associations for little people. `` I think it's a lot of fun,'' said the 4-foot-5 human projectile. `` If <PERSON> Eddie </PERSON> <PERSON> Murphy </PERSON> can make fun of being black, if <PERSON> Dom </PERSON> <PERSON> DeLuise </PERSON> can make fun of being fat, why not me? Why ca n't I make fun of being short? `` I'm into it. I'm an entertainer.'' He also works as a welder and circus entertainer. `` I eat fire, eat nails, walk on broken glass,'' he said. <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON>, 27, is next slated for a show Sept. 13-15 at a downtown bar, <ORGANIZATION> Animal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, with a $ 1,000 prize for the winner. <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON>, who'll be wearing a crash helmet, knee pads and a harness for contestants to grab, says he'll be rooting for participants to outdistance the 7-feet, 8-inch distance he was tossed in a <LOCATION> Bradenton </LOCATION> bar last summer. Dwarfism groups hate the idea. `` From the standpoint of little people, it's demeaning,'' said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Etten </PERSON>, former president of <ORGANIZATION> Little </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION>, which represents about 4,000 dwarfs. `` It's mean-spirited. It moves us back to the Dark Ages. It's poking fun at a minority group,'' said <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Etten </PERSON>, noting that public outcry helped kill plans for a dwarf-throwing contest in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> in 1985 <ORGANIZATION> Manatee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commissioners </ORGANIZATION> did n't like the <LOCATION> Bradenton </LOCATION> dwarf toss, but could n't find a law under which they could ban it. `` I think we all pretty much fel