dent,'' he said. <PERSON> Carmen </PERSON> <PERSON> Malphrus </PERSON>, who was treated at a hospital and released, said she initially thought the cloud was harmless. `` I saw all these other cars going into the fog, so I just assumed it's not that thick, I guess, everyone's going into it,'' she said. `` Then once I was in it I realized there was no visibility. `` Then all of a sudden, bam, bam, bam, all of these cars started hitting each other. And then you heard screaming. It was a huge wreck,'' she said. `` Today was my birthday,'' she added. `` So maybe God just gave me a birthday present and let me live.''
